# 詞: 銀包

1. 我個銀包細到連一張十蚊紙都塞唔入去。 (My wallet is so small that it can't even fit a ten-dollar bill.)
2. 佢成日唔識儲錢，每個月收工銀包就空空如也。 (He never knows how to save money; his wallet is empty every month after payday.)
3. 唔好意思，我今日忘咗帶銀包出門，可以借我幾蚊搭車嗎？ (Sorry, I forgot to bring my wallet today. Can you lend me some money for the bus fare?)
4. 個賊企喺地鐵站，專登望住行人嘅銀包，企圖行竊。 (The thief stood at the MTR station, specifically watching people's wallets, attempting to pickpocket.)
5. 佢個銀包入面除咗張舊相，就冇其他嘢啦。 (Apart from an old photo, there's nothing else in his wallet.)
6. 買完呢件大衣，我個銀包即刻瘦咗一圈。 (After buying this coat, my wallet immediately lost a bit of its bulk.)
7. 佢成日話要買新銀包，但係始終都係用緊舊嗰個。 (He always says he wants to buy a new wallet, but he's still using the old one.)
8. 個銀包掉咗落街，希望有人拾到交返畀我。 (I dropped my wallet on the street; I hope someone picks it up and returns it to me.)
9. 佢個銀包設計好特別，係用回收膠樽做嘅。 (His wallet has a unique design; it's made from recycled plastic bottles.)
10. 雖然我個銀包冇幾多錢，但我覺得開心最重要。 (Although my wallet doesn't have much money, I think happiness is the most important thing.) [end of text]


